  "text": "In the long term, such problems have traditionally been solved by building new power plants and transmission lines, a solution that is costly to implement and that involves long construction times and opposition from pressure groups. It is envisaged that a new solution to such operational problems will rely on the upgrading of existing transmission corridors by using the latest power electronic equipment and methods, a new technological thinking that comes under the generic title of FACTSan acronym for flexible alternating current transmission systems [CITATION_1] .",
